statement.p:
Conditionally convergent series converge very slowly. As an example, consider the famous formulaWe will derive this formula in upcoming work.

              \frac{\pi}{4} = 1 - \frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{5} - \frac{1}{7} + \cdots = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} (-1)^{k} \frac{1}{2k+1}
            .

solution.p:
In this case we have

              |S_n - \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} (-1)^{k} \frac{1}{2k+1}| \lt  a_{n+1} = \frac{1}{2n+1}
            .

li.p:
Notice that \frac{1}{k} - \frac{1}{k^2} = \frac{k-1}{k^2}. So our series can be rewritten as

                  \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{k-1}{k^2}
                .
